“I think, with never-ending gratitude, that the young women of today do not and can never know at what price their right to free speech and to speak at all in public has been earned.” - Lucy Stone I try to keep my posts "good vibe zones". So, instead of finding the one thing in here you don't like and commenting only on that, also comment about something you DID like. Balance the negativity. Love you long time. So, I made a discord server. It's a relaxed environment where you can take/donate memes to the cause, play trivia twice a week, chat about lots of topics or about nothing at all. We also have Jack Box game night and are setting up movie night! Very laid back/relaxed vibe. item.title: Princess Etch 2025 recap!
item.description:
Greetings Imgurians! As the year comes to a close, I wanted to take the opportunity to look back on my year - much of which I shared here on Imgur - and celebrate some fun milestones with all of you!
The article is paywalled now, but if you're interested in checking it out you can read it here! https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2025/06/09/science/math-strogatz-taxi-geometry.html?unlocked_article_code=1.Nk8.uUuG.tfiF8w-lp3pt&smid=url-share
It has been nothing short of a pleasure to share this series with you - thank you all for your amazing receptiveness to this silly series!
Note to self: I need to do more Etch A Sketch drawings on non-red canvases
Wooooooh!
Some of you here on Imgur are responsible for my new web shop success! Thanks a bunch! https://princessetch.bigcartel.com/
KARP KARP KARP MAGIKARP KARP KARP
Then I got new hair! Turns out new hair is expensive! I've since let it fade but might muster the gumption to try a new color at some point! Weee!
The library workshops are the absolute best and if you know a librarian I am happy to send you workshop info and a free sticker in snail mail for freeee! DM me for deets.
Ripley's continues to be one of the coolest clients I've ever worked with! If you stop by an Odditorium there's a chance you'll spot a placard about me!
I end this year grateful for the community I've found here, and I can't wait to continue sharing my journey in 2026! My 10-year anniversary of full-time Etch A Sketch artistry will be on June 1st this coming year. I can't wait to celebrate with all of you!!!
